    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hey @dave-dm! Truffle manages versions of the Solidity compiler by storing them in `<homeDirectory>/.config/truffle/compilers/` on mac. I assume it is the same with Linux?\r\n\r\nIf you read the docs you probably already saw it but just in case you missed it, [here](https://www.trufflesuite.com/docs/truffle/reference/configuration#solc) are the docs on compiler configuration. Most notably is the option to specify a path to a local copy of the compiler which you will probably find useful for your setup. Let me know if you have any more questions!",
